<br>
Saddam is a bad person; maybe the good of removing him will overwhelm the bad of having to do it.<br>
<br>
Is one person's life worth a 1000?  Saddam has killed 5000 kurds, and that's only the kurds.<br>
<br>
Part of being a soldier is putting yourself in front of others who, for whatever reason, can't.<br>
<br>
Soldiers give up their freedom so other's can be free.  Sometimes that goes for their lives, too.  <br>
<br>
Maybe it isn't right.  But, maybe,just maybe, some little boy or girl will be able to look up at the sky and dream a dream Saddam would never have permitted him to live.<br>
